title: Remove Google Restriction
message:
Remove Google Restriction
Google added a new restriction in Android 5.1.1, disallowing apps to get a list of running processes. A work-around was added to the Native scanner to enable /proc sorting of Android/Linux processes. However some information cannot be found in /proc, like importance level for example. So to anyone wanting this information back, we add a small Xposed Hook that removes the restriction, again allowing the app to get the internal list of processes.

title: Fix issue with Android 5.1.1 or grater
message:
Fix issue with Android 5.1.1 or grater
Google removed access to Android Process details for regular apps in Android 5.1.1. Only applications installed at /system/priv-app can access this data now. This means that all that we have access to, is what can be found in /proc which in turn means fewer details about all Android processes. Luckily /proc does contain enough information to allow us to distinguish between Linux and Android processes.
